A vintage 1950s travel poster style illustration of a weary business traveler in a retro hotel room, slumped dramatically over an ornate wooden desk, staring at an old CRT computer monitor displaying a loading bar frozen at 3%. A decorative rotary telephone sits nearby. Through the window, a neon "HOTEL" sign glows against a night sky. A snail crawls across the desk toward the monitor, leaving a silvery trail. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones with visible halftone dots and aged paper texture throughout the composition.
